Value Seeds Limited, an indigenous crop seed production, solution, and development company, in collaboration with the Mastercard Foundation will empower 10,000 smallholder farmers in Nigeria with the distribution of farm supplements. Women will constitute 70% of the program 's participants who will be selected from 22 local governments in five states, including Kaduna, Kano, Niger, Benue, and Katsina. Read on.  Find out more about Mastercard Foundation in Africa.